      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's like you're trying to hold onto a part of yourself that's no longer there, and it's a painful reminder of what you've lost. It's natural to feel like you're being false to yourself, but the truth is, pretending to be someone you're not can be even more damaging to your mental health than being true to yourself. You don't need to pretend to be someone who's perfect; you can work on being the best version of yourself, flaws and all. If you're feeling so lost and broken, maybe it's time to start focusing on healing and growing, rather than trying to put on a mask for others.",
